SIMPLE: murrhine
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Murrhine
<hw>Mur"rhine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>murrhinus</ets>, fr. <ets>murrha</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>murrhin</ets>.]</ety> <def>Made of the stone or material called by
the Romans <xex>murrha</xex>; -- applied to certain costly vases of
great beauty and delicacy used by the luxurious in Rome as wine cups;
<as>as, <ex>murrhine</ex> vases, cups, vessels</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Murrhine glass</b></col>, <cd>glassware made in imitation
of murrhine vases and cups.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Murrion</ent>⟦br⟧
